div2.p:
In all, 3,020 volumes were studied, of which sixty-nine belong to the period after the
      Reformation. 1,705 volumes belong to the University Library; 448 to the Metropolitan Chapter;
      370 to Strahow monastery; 198 to the National Museum; eighty-four to the Augustines;
      seventy-nine to the Red Star Crusaders; fifty-nine to the Franciscans; thirty-two to the
      Capuchins; twenty-five to the Museum of Arts and Crafts; twelve to the Municipal Archives; and
      eight to the library of Prince Kinsky.

